 the firm does not believe that portfolios must be fully invested in stocks at all times they look for opportunities with favorable rewardrisk parameters the firm employs an opportunistic style that is responsive to changes in the markets guild continuously reevaluates the asset allocations and positions in their portfolios when opportunities arise guild utilizes foreign currencies and foreign currency denominated cash equivalents to earn income and to capture appreciation from foreign exchange trends the firm also looks for investments that offer the potential to appreciate  in  months and that have a perceived rewardrisk potential of  to  in the news ari cohn is no longer serving in their position at guild investment management inc june    •  relsci guild investment management inc disclosed a new stake in pfizer inc in a filing on march   may    •  relsci guild investment management inc disclosed in a filing on march   that it reduced its stake in snapon inc april    •  relsci guild investment management inc » guild investment management is a global value manager the firm seeks to identify opportunities for capital appreciation and income through investments in the stocks of us and nonus companies etfs and index shares of us markets and commodities foreign currency deposits or forwards and other foreign currency denominated securities including bonds cash equivalents index shares or derivatives instrumentsguild examines the global markets to identify macroeconomic and sociopolitical or demographic changes or trends that provide opportunities in countries sectors industries and companies once they have identified these opportunities guild employs bottomup fundamental research on target companies to determine their potential for appreciation the firm prefers to invest in the stocks of undervalued companies that are operating in growing industries they look for companies that are trading at pe ratios below their expected percentage rate of earnings growth guild looks